What is Feature Scaling?
🔹 Definition

Feature Scaling is a technique used to standardize or normalize numerical features so they fall within a similar range.

🔹 Why is it needed?

Many machine learning algorithms are sensitive to feature magnitude.
If one feature has a large range (Salary: 40,000) and another has a small range (CGPA: 8), the larger one dominates the model.

🔹 Pipeline Position

Feature Scaling is usually done:

After handling missing values

After encoding categorical variables

Just before feeding data into the ML model

