3️⃣ Why Feature Scaling is Important
🔹 Distance-Based Algorithms Problem

Algorithms like:

K-Nearest Neighbours (KNN)

K-Means

SVM

Use Euclidean distance.

If:

Age = 20

Salary = 40,000

Distance calculation will be dominated by Salary.

After scaling → both contribute equally.

4️⃣ Impact on Different Algorithms
Algorithm	Scaling Required?	Reason
KNN	✅ Yes	Uses distance
SVM	✅ Yes	Margin depends on scale
Logistic Regression	✅ Yes	Uses gradient descent
PCA	✅ Yes	Captures variance
Neural Networks	✅ Yes	Faster convergence
Decision Trees	❌ No	Uses split comparisons
Random Forest	❌ No	Tree-based
XGBoost	❌ No	Tree-based
5️⃣ Effect on Model Performance

Example:

Logistic Regression
Without scaling → 65% accuracy
With scaling → 86% accuracy

Decision Trees
Accuracy remains same (scale-invariant)

6️⃣ Handling Outliers

⚠ Important:

Standardization does NOT remove outliers.

If an extreme value exists:

It remains extreme after scaling.

It just moves to a different numerical scale.

To handle outliers:

Use Robust Scaling

Or remove outliers separately

7️⃣ When Must You Use Standardization?
✅ Must Use:

KNN

SVM

PCA

Neural Networks

Gradient Descent based models

❌ Not Necessary:

Decision Trees

Random Forest

Gradient Boosted Trees
